  against the liabilities that the trustee may incur working as a registered trustee;
 (f) the trustee is issued with a notice under section  40-40 of Schedule 2 to the Corporations Act 2001 (a show-cause notice) in relation to the trustee&#39;s registration as a liquidator under that Act;
 (g) the trustee&#39;s registration as a liquidator under the Corporations Act 2001 is suspended or cancelled;
 (h) any other event prescribed.
The notice must be lodged within 5 business days after the registered trustee could reasonably be expected to be aware that the event has occurred.
Offence
 (2) A person commits an offence if:
